<p>128.<br/>It was at BOHAIN I left the Unit after a very trying time including the taking of the Hindenburg Line. Our Artillery were covering 2 Divisions of Yanks the Infantry were back resting after the <strike>severest</strike> capture of the LINE.</p>
<p>The change to England was very welcome although it hurt a little leaving all my pals.</p>
<p>On arrival in England (Parkhouse Camp) I met Capt Glasgow who was Adjt &amp; he detailed me for duty at Weymouth for which I will be forever grateful. It proved an excellent place- a pleasure resort on the coast &amp; known as the Naples of England. I spent many</p>
